annotationA: Ubiquitin-60S ribosomal protein L40; Ubiquitin: exists either covalently attached to another protein, or free (unanchored). When covalently bound, it is conjugated to target proteins via an isopeptide bond either as a monomer (monoubiquitin), a polymer linked via different Lys residues of the ubiquitin (polyubiquitin chains) or a linear polymer linked via the initiator Met of the ubiquitin (linear polyubiquitin chains). annotationB: Regulatory particle triple-A ATPase 4 (Rpt4) is the 19S proteasomal ATPase, which is a component of the 26S proteosome complex. Rpt4 localizes to the nucleolus and participates in regulating rRNA transcription. Rpt4 physically interacts with the BHD tumor suppressor
